{"lemma":"صَحِيحٌ","slug":"صَحِيحٌ","root":"ص.ح.ح","root_slug":"ص-ح-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ح-ح","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23764"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AD%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"complete, perfect, whole"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sound, healthy","examples":[{"text":"الصِّحَّةُ تَاجٌ عَلَى رُؤُوسِ الْأَصِحَّاءِ لَا يَرَاهُ إِلَّا الْمَرْضَى.","english":"Health is a crown on the heads of the healthy, that only the ill can see."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"correct"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"true"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"authentic"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"valid"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"regular"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"genuine"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare صَحَّ (ṣaḥḥa, “to be healthy, to be correct”). Cognate with Hebrew צח (tsákh, “pure, unblemished”)."},"ipa":["/sˤa.ħiːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23764","headword_ar":"صَحِيحٌ","root":"SH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, MA, Msb, K, KL) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAHN","text_ar":"صَحَاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Healthy, sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, MA, K, KL;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHu Aljasadi","text_ar":"صَحِيحُ الجَسَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a man: (Msb:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound, valid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substantial, real, sure, certain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true, right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL, and Msb in explanation of the former word,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct, just"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, whole"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL,) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unmarred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unimpaired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from every imperfection"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blemish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and from everything that would occasion doubt"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suspicion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil opinion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) [and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suitable to the case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1:)] fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHapN","text_ar":"صَحِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman [and to other things]: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAHN","text_ar":"صَحَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, K,) a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHN","text_ar":"صَحِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and applied to men [and other things], (A, K, TA,) and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHapN","text_ar":"صَحِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and applied to women, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSiH~aA='u","text_ar":"اَصِحَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, K,) a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHN","text_ar":"صَحِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and applied to men, (A, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSiH~apN","text_ar":"اَصِحَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", likewise applied to men, (A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAy^iHu","text_ar":"صَحَايِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHapN","text_ar":"صَحِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and applied to women. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHu AlA^adiymi","text_ar":"صَحِيحُ الاَدِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sound of skin;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAHu","text_ar":"صَحَاحُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^adiymi","text_ar":"الاَدِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [but each has a tropical signification; for] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN SaHiyHu AlA^adiymi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ صَحِيحُ الاَدِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 628) meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of origin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 135.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirohamN SaHiyHN","text_ar":"دِرْهَمٌ صَحِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dirhem free from defect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAHN","text_ar":"صَحَاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuHaAHN","text_ar":"صُحَاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which I find as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHN","text_ar":"صَحِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in my copy of the K,] with damm, is allowable, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwaAlN","text_ar":"طُوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawiylN","text_ar":"طَوِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) And it is said in a trad., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuqaAsimu A@bonu A=dama A^ahola Aln~aAri qisomapF SaHaAHFA","text_ar":"يُقَاسِمُ ا@بْنُ ا=دَمَ اَهْلَ النَّارِ قِسْمَةً صَحَاحًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The son of Adam,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning Kábeel [or Cain], who slew his brother Hábeel [or Abel],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will make a right division with the people of Hell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that half of it shall be for him, and half for them. (L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","MA","Msb","K","KL","L","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B5%D8%AD%D9%8A%D8%AD/","headword_ar":"صحيح","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23355#7c4265","body_html":"<span>الصحيح: هو الذي ليس في مقابلة الفاء والعين واللام حرف علة وهمزة وتضعيف، وعند النحويين هو اسم لم يكن في آخره حرف علة.<br></span><br>الصحيح في العبادات والمعاملات: ما اجتمعت أركانه وشرائطه حتى يكون معتبرًا في حق الحكم.<br><br>الصحيح: ما يعتمد عليه.<br><br>الصحيح من الحديث: ما مر في الحديث الصحيح."}]}}